Dark Chocolate Cake

1 3/4 cups S R flour
pinch salt
1/2 tsp bicarb soda
1 1/4 cups sugar
1/2 cup cocoa
100g butter
2 eggs
1 cup milk
1 tsp vanilla

Sift flour, cocoa, sugar, bicarb and salt into bowl - combine dry ingredients.

Melt butter over low heat. Add to flour along with vanilla, eggs and milk, beat a further 2 minutes.

Place in 8" round cake tin and bake in moderate oven 180c for 40-45 mins.

Ice when cool.


Icing - Chocolate ganache

http://www.taste.com.au/recipes/7797/chocolate+ganache

I replaced the dark cooking chocolate with Lindt Orange (probably why it tasted so good:)
